t Salmon]]<br><small>R-[[Arizona]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of current members of the United States House of Representatives by seniority|United States Representatives by seniority]]|years=192nd}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Jason Chaffetz]]<br><small>R-[[Utah]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{USHouseCurrent}}\n{{SC-FedRep}}\n{{USCongRep-start|congresses= 104th\u2013106th & 113th\u2013114th [[United States Congress]]es |state=[[South Carolina]]}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/104}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/105}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/106}}\n{{USCongRep/Line}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/113}}\n{{USCongRep/SC/114}}\n{{USCongRep-end}}\n{{Governors of South Carolina}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sanford, Mark}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:American Episcopalians]]\n[[Category:Eagle Scouts]]\n[[Category:Furman University alumni]]\n[[Category:Goldman Sachs people]]\n[[Category:Governors of South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the United States House of Representatives from South Carolina]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Charleston, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:People from Beaufort County, South Carolina]]\n[[Category:People from Fort Lauderdale, Florida]]\n[[Category:People from Hillsborough County, Florida]]\n[[Category:South Carolina Republicans]]\n[[Category:United States Air Force officers]]\n[[Category:United States Air Force reservists]]\n[[Category:University of South Carolina trustees]]\n[[Category:University of Virginia alumni]]\n[[Category:Republican Party members of the United States House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:Republican Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]"}]}}}}